Singapore
Publish Start Date
Apr 27 2014
Job Level
Non-Professional (Will not auto post to LinkedIn)
|
Responsibilities:
Receive and check goods to ensure that incoming shipment match the purchase order.
Coordinate with vendors for the schedule of delivery and escalate any discrepancy in quantity and quality to immediate superior.
Ensure proper documentation, storage of goods and maintenance of material store in accordance to required safety standards.
Monitor and manage all raw materials and finish goods inventory.
Support project team by arranging for fabrication area, transferring materials to contractors for fabrication and assembly purpose as well as packing of projects.
Assist in all export pre-shipment and shipment arrangement, ensure right package are release and collected by forwarder.
Operate and maintain all material handling equipment.
Requirements:
ITC/NTC with minimum 1 year experience in store management.
Computer literate with knowledge in JDE / Oracle / SAP.
Good communication and interpersonal skills.
With forklift skill / license.